{"data": {"id": "scopus_85168083105", "publication_type_id": 5, "publication_type_label": "Artikel i vetenskaplig tidskrift", "ref_value": "ISREF", "title": "Improved syntheses of P2X<inf>7</inf> ligands based on substituted benzyl amide of pyroglutamic acid motif labelled with iodine-123 or iodine-125", "pubyear": "2023", "sourcetitle": "Journal of Radioanalytical and Nuclear Chemistry", "issn": "02365731", "eissn": null, "sourcevolume": null, "sourceissue": null, "sourcepages": null, "articlenumber": null, "abstract": "Abstract: P2X7 sites are emerging targets for molecular imaging research, notably in the\u00a0context of neurodegeneration and inflammatory conditions. Therefore, we prepared a\u00a0precursor for (radio)iodination of the P2X7 ligand VPGIS191. We then developed\u00a0a radioiodination method with 123I for SPECT with a radiochemical yield of 71 \u00b1 13% and 125I for autoradiography with a radiochemical yield of 85 \u00b1 6%\u00a0Autoradiography of [125I]VPGIS191 in mouse brain cryostat sections demonstrated\u00a0approximately 36 nM binding affinity and Bmax of approximately 400 pmol/gram tissue for P2X7 binding sites. VPGIS191 (cis) had a two-fold lower affinity compared to its geometric trans-isomer TZ6019. Graphical abstract: [Figure not available: see fulltext.]", "keywords": "Autoradiography, P2X  receptor 7, Radiopharmaceuticals, Single photon emission tomography", "publication_identifiers": [{"identifier_code": "scopus-id", "identifier_value": "85168083105"}, {"identifier_code": "doi", "identifier_value": "10.1007/s10967-023-09081-2"}], "authors": [{"affiliations": [{"scopus-afid": "60021588", "scopus-affilname": "University of Chemistry and Technology, Prague", "scopus-affiliation-city": "Prague", "scopus-affiliation-country": "Czech Republic"}], "person": [{"position": "1", "last_name": "Anna", "first_name": "Mare\u0161ov\u00e1", "identifiers": [{"type": "scopus-auth-id", "value": "57220780667"}]}]}, {"affiliations": [{"scopus-afid": "6002158